President Obama called Iraqi Prime Minister Nuri al-Maliki to congratulate the Iraqi people on the success of the Arab Summit hosted in Baghdad. They discussed the joint efforts of the United States and Iraq to advance peace and security in the region. They also talked about the political situation in Iraq and other shared interests. President Obama expressed support for a unified, democratic Iraq as defined by Iraq's constitution and for Prime Minister Maliki's participation in ongoing dialogue to reconcile Iraqi political blocs.